dwidth increased ~6.5x)\n\n  version = 24.1\n    (internal finalized version; expected post-upgrade)\n\nNo sql.defaults.* settings were found to differ from defaults.\n\n========================================\n3. ZONE CONFIGURATIONS (REPLICATION & GC TTL)\n========================================\n\n--- RANGE default ---\n  num_replicas: 3\n  gc.ttlseconds: 14400  (4 hours)\n  range_min_bytes: 134217728 (128 MiB)\n  range_max_bytes: 536870912 (512 MiB)\n\n--- RANGE liveness ---\n  num_replicas: 5\n  gc.ttlseconds: 600  (10 minutes)\n  range_min_bytes: 128 MiB | range_max_bytes: 512 MiB\n\n--- RANGE meta ---\n  num_replicas: 5\n  gc.ttlseconds: 3600  (1 hour)\n  range_min_bytes: 128 MiB | range_max_bytes: 512 MiB\n\n--- RANGE system ---\n  num_replicas: 5\n  gc.ttlseconds: 14400  (4 hours)\n  range_min_bytes: 128 MiB | range_max_bytes: 512 MiB\n\n--- DATABASE system ---\n  num_replicas: 5\n  gc.ttlseconds: 14400  (4 hours)\n  range_min_bytes: 128 MiB | range_max_bytes: 512 MiB\n\n--- TABLE defaultdb.tenant_b.table_c ---\n  num_replicas: 3\n  gc.ttlseconds: 14400  (4 hours)\n\n--- TABLE defaultdb.tenant_b.table_d ---\n  num_replicas: 3\n  gc.ttlseconds: 14400  (4 hours)\n\n--- TABLE system.public.lease ---\n  gc.ttlseconds: 600  (10 minutes, overrides database default)\n\n--- TABLE system.public.replication_constraint_stats ---\n  gc.ttlseconds: 600  (10 minutes)\n\n--- TABLE system.public.replication_stats ---\n  gc.ttlseconds: 600  (10 minutes)\n\n--- TABLE system.public.span_stats_tenant_boundaries ---\n  gc.ttlseconds: 3600  (1 hour)\n\n--- TABLE system.public.statement_activity ---\n  gc.ttlseconds: 3600  (1 hour)\n\n--- TABLE system.public.statement_statistics ---\n  gc.ttlseconds: 3600  (1 hour)\n\n--- TABLE system.public.tenant_usage ---\n  gc.ttlseconds: 7200  (2 hours)\n\n--- TABLE system.public.transaction_activity ---\n  gc.ttlseconds: 3600  (1 hour)\n\n--- TABLE system.public.transaction_statistics ---\n  gc.ttlseconds: 3600  (1 hour)\n\n========================================\n4. SUMMARY OF NON-DEFAULT TUNING\n========================================\n  - kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate raised to 208 MiB (was 32 MiB): aggressive\n    rebalancing bandwidth — suitable for bulk data movement or post-restore\n    recovery; may saturate network during rebalance storms.\n  - kv.range_merge.queue.enabled = false: range merges are suppressed, keeping\n    ranges fragmented. Common practice to avoid churn after bulk deletes, but\n    prevents automatic space reclamation.\n  - diagnostics.reporting.enabled = true: external telemetry is active. Confirm\n    this is acceptable under data-residency or privacy requirements.\n  - liveness/meta/system ranges use num_replicas=5 (higher than the 3-replica\n    default), providing extra fault tolerance for critical system ranges.\n  - Custom zone configs on defaultdb.tenant_b.table_c and table_d (num_replicas=3,\n    gc.ttlseconds=14400) indicate tenant-specific table configuration is in place.\n\n========================================\n5. AUDIT SCOPE & ATTESTATION\n========================================\nThis audit is READ-ONLY. No cluster settings, zone configurations, replica\ncounts, or Kubernetes resources were modified. The cluster state is unchanged\nfrom the state observed at audit time.\n\nData collected via:\n  kubectl exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach node status --certs-dir=...\n  kubectl exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=... -e \"SELECT ... FROM crdb_internal.cluster_settings ...\"\n  kubectl exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=... -e \"SELECT ... FROM crdb_internal.zones ...\"\n  kubectl -n cockroachdb get statefulset crdb-cluster\nAUDIT_EOF\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with full findings report"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2281,"cache_read_input_tokens":29659,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_